I don't think this benchmark is valid. In general you are not supposed to perform same operation in a loop like this, rather let JMH do that. Re-writing the benchmark to remove the loop shows same performance for these two operations:
    @Benchmark
    public boolean lookupInExclusive(BenchmarkBytesValues.BenchmarkData data)
    {
        return data.exclusiveFilter.testBytes(word, 0, 3);
    }

    @Benchmark
    public boolean lookupInMultiRange(BenchmarkBytesValues.BenchmarkData data)
    {
        return data.multiRangeFilter.testBytes(word, 0, 3);
    }

